# Time Tracking Phase 3 - Manual Testing Guide

**Version:** 1.0
**Date:** 2025-01-22
**Coverage:** Phase 3.0-3.5 Features
**Status:** Ready for Testing

---

## Overview

This guide provides comprehensive manual testing procedures for all Phase 3 time tracking features. Each test includes prerequisites, steps, and expected results.

**Feature Coverage:**
- ✅ Project System (3.0)
- ✅ Manual Time Entry (3.1)
- ✅ Monthly Reporting (3.2)
- ✅ Export & Bulk Operations (3.3)
- ✅ Calendar View (3.4)
- ✅ Undo System & Polish (3.5)

---

## Test Environment Setup

**Prerequisites:**
1. Dev server running: `npm run dev`
2. Browser with DevTools open (check console for errors)
3. Clean IndexedDB state (or existing test data)
4. Both light and dark mode testing

**Test Data Recommendations:**
- At least 3 projects with different colors
- At least 20 time entries spanning 2+ weeks
- Mix of entries with/without projects
- Mix of entries with/without notes

---

## Test Suite 1: Project System (Phase 3.0)

### Test 1.1: Create Project

**Steps:**
1. Navigate to Time Tracking page
2. Click "Projects" tab
3. Click "Create Project" button
4. Fill in project details:
   - Name: "Test Project Alpha"
   - Color: Select blue (#45B7D1)
   - Description: "Testing project creation"
5. Click "Create Project"

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ Project appears in project list
- ✅ Color dot displays correctly next to name
- ✅ Success message or visual feedback
- ✅ Project appears in project selectors throughout app

**Dark Mode Verification:**
- ✅ All text readable in dark mode
- ✅ Color dot visible against dark background

---

### Test 1.2: Edit Project

**Steps:**
1. In Projects tab, click "Edit" on existing project
2. Change name to "Test Project Beta"
3. Change color to orange (#FFA07A)
4. Update description
5. Click "Save"

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ Changes persist in project list
- ✅ Time entries with this project show updated color
- ✅ No data loss or corruption

---

### Test 1.3: Delete Project

**Steps:**
1. Create a new project "Temp Project"
2. Assign it to 2-3 time entries
3. Click "Delete" on the project
4. Confirm deletion in modal

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ Project removed from list
- ✅ Time entries with this project show "No Project" or project ID
- ✅ No broken references in database
- ✅ Other projects unaffected

---

### Test 1.4: Project Selector (Timer)

**Steps:**
1. Go to Time Tracking page, "Timer" tab
2. Click project selector dropdown
3. Select "Test Project Alpha"
4. Start timer
5. Stop timer after 10 seconds

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ Project dropdown shows all active projects
- ✅ Selected project displays with color dot
- ✅ New time entry has project assigned
- ✅ Recent entries show project name and color

---

### Test 1.5: Project Filter

**Steps:**
1. Go to "Entries" tab
2. Open project filter dropdown
3. Select "Test Project Alpha"
4. Verify filtered results
5. Change to "Test Project Beta"
6. Select "All Projects" to clear filter

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ Only entries matching selected project display
- ✅ Entry count updates correctly
- ✅ Filter persists during pagination
- ✅ "All Projects" shows all entries

---

## Test Suite 2: Manual Time Entry (Phase 3.1)

### Test 2.1: Create Manual Entry (End Time Mode)

**Steps:**
1. Click "Manual Entry" button in timer panel
2. Fill in fields:
   - Description: "Manual test entry"
   - Project: "Test Project Alpha"
   - Start: Today at 09:00
   - End: Today at 10:30
3. Click "Create Entry"

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ Modal closes
- ✅ New entry appears in entries list
- ✅ Duration calculated correctly (1h 30m)
- ✅ Project assigned correctly
- ✅ Start/end times match input

---

### Test 2.2: Create Manual Entry (Duration Mode)

**Steps:**
1. Click "Manual Entry" button
2. Fill in fields:
   - Description: "Duration mode test"
   - Project: None
   - Start: Today at 14:00
   - Duration: 2h 15m
3. Click "Create Entry"

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ End time auto-calculated (16:15)
- ✅ Duration preview shows "2h 15m"
- ✅ Entry saved with correct times
- ✅ No project assigned (shows blank/dash)

---

### Test 2.3: Validation - End Before Start

**Steps:**
1. Open manual entry modal
2. Set start time: Today at 15:00
3. Set end time: Today at 14:00
4. Try to save

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ Error message: "End time must be after start time"
- ✅ Form does not submit
- ✅ No invalid entry created

---

### Test 2.4: Validation - Missing Required Fields

**Steps:**
1. Open manual entry modal
2. Leave description blank
3. Set times
4. Try to save

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ Error message: "Description is required"
- ✅ Form does not submit

**Repeat with:**
- Missing start time
- Missing end time (in end time mode)
- Missing duration (in duration mode)

---

### Test 2.5: Manual Entry with Notes

**Steps:**
1. Create manual entry with all fields
2. Add detailed notes: "This is a test entry with comprehensive notes to verify the notes field works correctly across all views."
3. Save entry
4. View entry in list (click to expand)
5. Edit entry and verify notes preserved

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ Notes saved correctly
- ✅ Notes visible in entry details
- ✅ Notes preserved during edit
- ✅ Notes appear in exported CSV

---

## Test Suite 3: Monthly Reporting (Phase 3.2)

### Test 3.1: Monthly Report View

**Steps:**
1. Go to "Reports" tab
2. Select "Monthly" view
3. Verify current month displays
4. Check daily breakdown grid

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ 28-31 day grid based on month
- ✅ Daily totals show correct durations
- ✅ Today's date highlighted
- ✅ Weekend days visually distinct
- ✅ Monthly total card displays

---

### Test 3.2: Monthly Navigation

**Steps:**
1. In monthly report, click "Previous Month"
2. Verify data changes to previous month
3. Click "Next Month" twice
4. Click "Today" button

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ Month/year updates in header
- ✅ Daily data recalculates correctly
- ✅ "Today" returns to current month
- ✅ No data corruption during navigation

---

### Test 3.3: Project Breakdown

**Steps:**
1. In monthly report, scroll to "Time by Project" section
2. Verify all projects listed
3. Check percentages sum to 100%
4. Hover over progress bars

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ All projects with time show in breakdown
- ✅ Percentages accurate (±0.1% rounding)
- ✅ Project colors match project settings
- ✅ Duration totals match monthly total
- ✅ "No Project" time shown if any exists

---

### Test 3.4: Heat Map Visualization

**Steps:**
1. Create entries on multiple days with varying durations:
   - Day 1: 2 hours
   - Day 2: 6 hours
   - Day 3: 10 hours
   - Day 4: 1 hour
2. View monthly report
3. Observe heat map intensity

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ Higher durations = darker/more intense colors
- ✅ Visual gradient is intuitive
- ✅ Hover shows exact duration
- ✅ Zero-duration days have minimal/no color

---

## Test Suite 4: Export & Bulk Operations (Phase 3.3)

### Test 4.1: CSV Export (All Entries)

**Steps:**
1. Go to "Entries" tab
2. Clear all filters
3. Click "Export CSV" button
4. Save file
5. Open in Excel or Google Sheets

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ File downloads as `time-entries-YYYY-MM-DD.csv`
- ✅ All entries exported
- ✅ Columns: Date, Start, End, Duration, Description, Project, Notes
- ✅ Dates formatted correctly (YYYY-MM-DD)
- ✅ Times formatted correctly (HH:MM)
- ✅ Duration formatted (Xh Ym)
- ✅ UTF-8 encoding (special characters preserved)
- ✅ Commas in descriptions properly escaped

---

### Test 4.2: CSV Export (Filtered Entries)

**Steps:**
1. Apply filters:
   - Project: "Test Project Alpha"
   - Date range: Last 7 days
2. Click "Export CSV"
3. Open exported file

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ Only filtered entries exported
- ✅ File name includes filter info or date
- ✅ Entry count matches visible entries

---

### Test 4.3: Bulk Select

**Steps:**
1. In entries list, check 5 entry checkboxes
2. Verify bulk actions bar appears
3. Click "Select All" button
4. Click "Clear Selection"

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ Individual checkboxes toggle selection
- ✅ Bulk actions bar shows count
- ✅ "Select All" selects all visible entries
- ✅ "Clear Selection" unchecks all
- ✅ Selection state visual feedback

---

### Test 4.4: Bulk Delete

**Steps:**
1. Select 3 time entries
2. Click "Delete" in bulk actions bar
3. Wait for undo toast to appear
4. Let toast auto-expire (10 seconds)

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ Entries removed from list immediately
- ✅ Undo toast shows "3 entries deleted"
- ✅ Entry count updates
- ✅ Toast auto-dismisses after 10 seconds
- ✅ Entries permanently deleted after expiry

---

### Test 4.5: Bulk Update Project

**Steps:**
1. Select 5 entries with different projects
2. Click "Change Project" in bulk actions bar
3. Select "Test Project Beta"
4. Confirm action

**Expected Results:**
- ✅ All selected entries now show "Test Project Beta"
- ✅ Project colors update in list
- ✅ Undo toast appears
- ✅ Monthly report updates with new project distribution

---

